cz.agents.alite.event
Class EventProcessor

java.lang.Object
  cz.agents.alite.event.EventProcessor

public class EventProcessor
extends java.lang.Object

The event processor is a wrapper for an event-queue cycle. On the fly, the processor lines up events added into it, and "sends" them to their particular recipients in a particular order. By sending, it is meant to call a EventHandler.handleEvent() method, with the event as an argument. An event handler needs to be registered into the processor to receive the events. The event is sent to all event handlers registered with the EventProcessor, if its recipient is null and it is sent to the particular event handler otherwise. The event-queue cycle can be paused/un-paused by the setRunning() method. By the default, the cycle is started running. The time of currently processed events can be obtained by the getCurrentTime() method.

Author:
Antonin Komenda
